      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;instruction&#34;&gt;Instruction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is how to setup a homepage hosted in the Github pages with &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/&#34;&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-hugo&#34;&gt;Install Hugo&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please follow this &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/installation/&#34;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt; to install Hugo. My platform is Ubuntu and I use the following command line installing Hugo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo snap install hugo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;create-the-static-website&#34;&gt;Create the static website&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use the &lt;code&gt;hugo&lt;/code&gt; command to create your static website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;hugo new site homepage --format yaml
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run the below command to have a test locally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;hugo server
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;create-a-homepage-in-github&#34;&gt;Create a homepage in Github&lt;/h2&gt;
